On July 2, 2013, over 500 Colorado citizens will engage in an act of mass civil disobedience to demonstrate the foolish, arbitrary, capricious and unconstitutional nature of the HB 13-1224 which will have gone into effect on the day before.

These Colorado citizens will gather in a public park in Aurora, Colorado. There are millions of such magazines in Colorado, and they have been lawfully owned and used by Colorado citizens for defense, sport, target shooting, competition, and other lawful use for decades. title: For Sale:  Night Optics M845 2.8x Gen2+ Night Vision Scope
postcontent:
For sale is a Night Optics M845 2.8x fixed magnification Gen 2+ night vision scope. I originally purchased one of these from OpticsPlanet.com last May, however it had a faulty wiring issue and the battery connections looked poor so the unit was sent back to the manufacturer, Night Optics, shortly after for inspection and repair. They sent me a replacement unit with different SN, brand new, direct from the manufacturer (not even through Optics Planet). I should have ordered from them in the first place, as it appeared OP was selling ones that didn't pass inspection or something along those lines.

None the less, the unit for sale is the brand new unit, straight from Night Optics. I have proof of purchase of original unit as well as the conversation with Night Optics to show that the unit was brand new, direct from Night Optics. I have not used yet on a rifle, but messed around with it for about half an hour outside. For an expensive piece of equipment such as night vision I though the background of the unit would be of utmost importance, especially since night vision tubes have a limited life.

That said, the quality of these units is AMAZING. The tubes do rival the quality and clearness of a true Gen 3 tube, but without the full price tag of one of those units. This was one of the few Gen 2 units sold and recommended by Tactical Night Vision Company (TNVC), until they were discontinued by Night Optics recently. The batteries were not installed in the unit during the brief time I've had this in storage in the safe.

Two nice features of this device are the eyeguard and the lens cap. The eyeguard closes when not in use to prevent green backsplash onto your face. The lens cap has a pin hole in it for safe and easy zeroing during daylight.

The only reason I am selling it is to upgrade to a PVS-14 to work with my current optic set up.

The one beauty of the M845 though, is that if you don't have an optic already, it is a night vision sight and optic all in one. There is a setting for just night vision, and three different intensity red dots reticles. Very easy to focus this unit as well.

Included is Scope, carrying case, 2 original batteries, lens paper, and instruction card.

Can send more pics if needed.

Other than the 30 minutes I used this in my yard this unit is brand new.

postcontent: Very attractive, rarely seen variant of the Smith & Wesson .38 Centennial Airweight, model 442. Very few Smith & Wesson 442 revolvers were manufactured in 1993 in any finish, much less satin nickel. Model marking inside the frame has no engineering change suffix, either. As far as basic features, The Model 442 is full-time double action; since the hammer is completely enclosed inside the frame. For personal protection, many veteran law enforcement officers and firearms instructors recommend the Centennial it cannot be fired in single action mode, where a person cocks the hammer and then pulls the trigger. This configuration has long been very popular and, in my opinion, vastly less dangerous than many of its semi-automatic peers. This revolver was made in 1993 and looks and works as new. title: For Sale:  You've bought an AR, now what? CIVILIAN CARBINE COURSE
location: North Central Ohio, Ohio, United States
postcontent:
You bought an AR, now what? This course is a must take!

Saturday, April 27, 2013 – Butler, Ohio (near Mansfield) - $100 per shooter.

Mid-Ohio Personal Defense Solutions is very excited to announce Mid-Ohio's Only Carbine Course. This course is taught by experienced NRA certified instructors and trainers. 

Recent events and the legislative response have created an unprecedented demand for AR variant and similar carbines. Many of the purchasers are first time carbine owners with a lot to learn. The defensive/tactical carbine is unique weapon system with a steep learning curve. Here is your chance to shorten that curve. If you are a first time AR or carbine owner, or an experienced shooter who would like to take your game to the next level, this course is a must.

The Defensive Carbine Course is designed to provide each student with the core skills needed to properly and effectively utilize an AR based carbine both safely and effective manner in both defensive and sporting applications.

This intense one-day (8-hour) course will include:
•	Safety
•	History of the AR Platform
•	Nomenclature
•	Carbine Function and Design
•	Operation and Manipulation
•	Ammunition Selection
•	Ballistics
•	Optics and sighting
•	Trigger Control
•	Proper Shooting Positions
•	Precision Shooting to 50 Yards
•	Close Quarter Battle Drills
•	Malfunctions and Resolutions
•	Balancing Speed vs. Accuracy
•	Personal / Home Defense Considerations

This course includes 4 hours of practical instruction, followed by 4 hours of practical application and shooting at our shooting range.

This course is primarily designed for the AR platform. However, students are welcomed to bring any other serviceable carbines such as, AK's Mini-14s, SK/SKS, etc. Please understand that portions of the course may not apply to these specific weapon systems.

Required Equipment:
•	Serviceable Carbine
•	Minimum 2 Magazines
•	Minimum 200 rounds of factory ammunition – NO RELOADS!
•	Eye Protection
•	Hearing Protection 

This course will be held in Butler, Ohio (near Mansfield, about 1 hour north of Columbus & 1 hour south of Cleveland), with the classroom portion being taught at the Worthington Township Fire Department and the shooting taking place at our private outdoor range about 5 minutes from the fire station. Space is limited. Please contact us today!

title: For Sale:  Factory Cased Engraved Colt Single Action Army Buntline Special Revolver with Factory Letter and Ivo
postcontent:
This weapon was Manufactured in 1984. The revolver features factory Class "B" floral scroll and punch dot engraving on the barrel, ejector rod housing, frame, cylinder flats, back strap and trigger guard. The top of the barrel is marked with the one line address, "COLT BUNTLINE SPECIAL .45" on the left side and the two line, three patent dates are marked on the left side of the frame followed by the Rampant Colt. The matching serial number is marked on the bottom of the frame and on the left side of the grip straps under the grips. Standard blade front and frame notch rear sights, all nickel finish and fitted with checkered ivory grips with gold Colt medallions. The left side of the front strap under the grip is marked "COLT ENG". The inside of the grips are marked with a number in red and "WOODWARD/SAA 45/FACTORY" and "GOLD". The accompanying factory letter verifies the serial number, caliber, barrel length, nickel finish, grips as smooth rosewood with silver Rampant Colt medallions at the time of shipment, factory Class "B" engraving and that it was shipped as 1 to John Jovino Co., 5 Centre Market Place, New York, N.Y. on May 25, 1984. There is also a hand written note with "R.L. WILSON" letterhead, dated Sept. 8, 1989 which states that "The Buntlines grips have been refitted by Al White himself." Complete with a Colt wooden case with royal blue velvet lining, with the green box label inside and Colt Heritage box with hand written end label matching the gun. In addition the end label has "No 8 of 26". A separate Colt letter dated January 12, 1989, states that the "Engraving is performed in our Custom Shop and is usually done at the request of the customer. I do not know what "8 of 26" signifies. When a firearm is shipped from the Custom Shop, the box is marked with a green label." 
BBL: 12 inch round 
Stock: 
Gauge: 45 LC 
Finish: nickel 
Grips: ivory 
Serial Number: SA43208


Condition: Excellent. The revolver retains virtually all of the original nickel finish with pin prick type blistering beginning on the underside of the barrel. There is a very faint drag line on the cylinder and a few overall scattered light scratches and handling marks. The grips excellent with a few hairline age cracks beginning to develop and sharp checkering. The engraving is sharp. The action is excellent. The case and box are both excellent.

title: For Sale:  SCAM alert!
postcontent:
If you reply to a post and get a response from an email of firearm001@yahoo.com, his name (so he says) is Xavier Bridges..14410 RIO BRAVO RD.,  MORENO VALLEY CA, 92553
He claims he is selling firearms at great price (HK 556A1 for $2000) because his wife was in an accident.  When I told him I though his ad seemed a little like a scam, he insists you make payment to him through transfer directly to him, and will not let you send money to the FFL he would be shipping the gun through.  When I told him I work at the FBI (which I do) and would pass his email information along to agents his emails promptly stopped.  Until then he kept sending emails (total about 5) asking for me to send the payment immediately.  
He may try to put more realistic prices on posts so as to not seem like a scam artist, but beware if you get email from him as I am SURE it is a scam to steal money from you.  Oh yeah and he likes to say he is a god fearing man as if that will help us believe and trust him!

The revolver has floral scroll engraving, with a punch dot background on the barrel, cylinder flats, frame, trigger guard and grip straps, with a feather design on the top strap. The style is very similar to that of Winchester Master Engraver Nick Kusmit.
